Text:
Make yourselves useful
or you'll be food too!

Such a sumptuous feast...
Mistress will be pleased!
Their aether will make me strong!
I shall show you something special!
For the honor of House Fortemps!
In Halone's name, I strike thee!
I will not waste this second chance.
That was a close call, ribbit!
I'll cut you down to size!
I hope you like it scorching!
Trust yourself, and trust your spear!
My all, I bring to bear!
I can dish it out too if needs be!
Healing winds, bring succor to all!
There's still fight left in you!

What a stench...
I shall have to burn these clothes.

Careful!
That big one looks nasty!
Is there no end to this foul menagerie!?
Best give that a wide berth...
'Tis all in such a sorry state of disrepair.
Did those rolling boulders just sprout legs!?
After you. I've an aversion to needles.
Is this a lair or a holding pen?
Who knows what we shall find!
Have we reached a dead end?
We must be deep in the heart of the aqueducts...

Not that way.
The debris is impassable.

What did I do!?
Did we trip the defenses!?
The sentinels still guard their post...

Aaah!
W-Was that not the right answer!?
This boulder is wedged in tightly...yes?
We must be deep in the heart of the aqueducts...

Not that way.
The debris is impassable.

Snakes!?
Why must it be snakes...?
Well, right or wrong, the door lies open!

Quite an expansive abode.
Shall we try upstairs?

This has the look of
a stage or arena...

This has the look of
a stage or arena...
Let us take a peek, shall we?
Now to see what it was guarding...
I find myself drawn to this one...
We can walk through this pipe, I think.
They'll not let us pass without a fight...
Our respite was short-lived, I see.
The fruit must have drawn them here...
Why would Mother's familiar be here...?

Still more?
Every ilm of this place is infested!
By my strength be healed, Brother!
I bid you dance with the flowers!
Take your ease among the trees.
O spears innumerable, rain down upon mine enemy!
O spears innumerable, leave naught unpierced!
Rest easy, Sister. You have done enough.
Entrust your fate to mine now, Brother!
It certainly kept us on our toes!
I'm not losing to you again!
Behold the power of the dragoon!
If he would taste my lance again, so be it.
Back, ere we burn to ashes!
Our foe is formidable. Have care.
We will not yield quite so easily!
Let us end this here and now!
Now the battle begins in earnest.
We've come too far to lose now!
Where has he run off to...? Best we keep on our guard.
Surely, he's no match for us.
So, their leader was a Sahagin? An easy victory, then.
There's something unsettling about this place...
I have a bad feeling about this.
We've nothing to be afraid of...right?
We would do well not to disturb the dead.
I'll not let you fall. Just focus on the voidsent.
No matter our foe, so long as we fight as one, we will prevail.
That a body could be so defiled... It's unforgivable!
It's so cool and damp. You would never guess this mine is in Thanalan.
I can't be the only one worried about the mine collapsing...right?
Do you suppose there are any deposits left untapped?
The air is so still. Are we certain there's anyone in here?
A fearsome foe, to be sure, but I don't think it's their leader.
Looks like we'll need more firesand.
Hm, no firesand. Perhaps there's more in the other room.
By the Twelve, what is that!?
At last, their leader shows himself!
We will not yield to the flames!
We've not trained for this, but we're ready. I know it!
Pay no heed to the flames─I will tend to your wounds.
I like not the looks of that nail. Quickly, we must destroy it!
I sense a terrible power in that nail.
Something feels wrong about this place...
Another dark and dreary dungeon... Wonderful.
Gods, would you look at the size of this place.
An ill wind blows through here. Let us hurry and be about our business.
Fear not─I will deal with its poison.
I would hate to get lost in here.
Dark forces are at work here.
Perhaps there's something useful in that room.
Do you suppose there's anything useful in that room?
Let's not waste any time with this one.
Their voidsent master has to be here somewhere.
I think we can use this flow of magic to return to the manor entrance.
So the lady of the manor reveals herself at last.
Let us put this wayward soul to rest.
We must hurry and save the goblins.
Let's get going. We have to help them!
Is there really a goblin settlement out here?
Nothing appears out of the ordinary. And yet...
I pray we're not too late.
With all these beasts lurking about, I hope the goblins are all right.
I was expecting Brayflox to be more...helpful.
Well, at least now the way forward is open.
The dragon! It won't escape this time!
Time to bring low the mountain.
The Lord of Crags... He's much more foreboding in person.
Don't let him unnerve you. Remember your training!
You'll not want for succor. I promise you that.
The heart is destroyed, but I fear we've only just begun.
It will take more than a few dragons to stop us.
They really have made a ruin of this place.
Stay vigilant. These dragons are said to be formidable.
Seven hells. I pray we don't face another of those beasts.
I was certain we were done for after that.
That's the wyvern that's been spouting fire all about the place.
So it was this dragon who set the halls ablaze.
Hopefully we've no more fires to worry about.
We'll need to be careful with this one.
What is this chill in the air?
Try not to get swept up in her gales!
Fierce winds befitting the Lady of the Vortex.
Together, we can weather this storm!
We can afford no missteps against the Garleans.
I fear my nerves may get the best of me.
We must watch out not only for soldiers, but magitek as well.
You'll not fall on my watch. Not here.
They will need more than magitek to stop us.
More soldiers. As if the magitek armor wasn't enough.
I'll see to your wounds. Just focus on the tribunus!
Now to find the Ultima Weapon, and shut it down.
We need but stick to the plan, and all will be well.
Our training has prepared us for this moment.
I'll not let my nerves get the better of me.
You're in good hands, my friends.
This magitek armor should do the job.
His hammer seems cumbersome, to say the least.
We've worked too hard to fail here!
This battle demands nothing less than our all!
This is the day we've been training for.
I will tend to your wounds. Now, go─finish this!
I can feel my strength returning!
We too can ride the wind!
We fight to protect our home! To protect Ishgard!
Let's finish this quickly, shall we?
I will see this through to the end. Upon my lance, I swear it!
We must bring our all to bear!
Halone, I beg you─grant us strength!
We must hold on! We must!
The barrier cannot suffer such an attack...
Let us show them the strength of Ishgard's finest!
Come what may, we must hold on!
